<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2016-04-01</DATELINE><TITLE>Crisis prevention and management by infection control nurses during the Middle East respiratory coronavirus outbreak in Korea</TITLE><BODY>A Middle East respiratory coronavirus (MERS-CoV) outbreak occurred in Korea between June 20 and July 28, 2015. A total of 186 patients were confirmed as being infected with MERS-CoV, 36 of whom died. Infection control nurses referred to hospital guidelines to address the screening and isolation needs of patients and instigated a variety of infection control activities to prevent MERS-CoV transmission at the frontlines of patient care. Their concerted effort is believed to have been instrumental in ending the outbreak.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>